text-help-one-title: How do I start swapping on ShwupIt?
text-help-one-desc: Starting is simple! Create an account, verify your email, and you're ready to list your first item or browse available swaps. Use the 'Shwup It' button on an item's page to initiate a swap.
text-help-two-title: Is there a fee to use ShwupIt?
text-help-two-desc: Joining ShwupIt is free! A non-refundable service fee of 5% is only applied when a swap is successfully completed to cover transaction and platform maintenance costs.
text-help-three-title: What items can I swap on ShwupIt?
text-help-three-desc: You can swap a wide range of items, including electronics, books, fashion items, and more. However, prohibited items include illegal substances, firearms, and any items that infringe on intellectual property rights.
text-help-four-title: How does ShwupIt ensure the safety and authenticity of swaps?
text-help-four-desc: We encourage user verification and offer a secure messaging system for clear communication. For added protection, we hold deposits in escrow until both parties confirm the swap's completion. Users are encouraged to report any suspicious activities.
text-help-five-title: What happens if there's a dispute in a swap?
text-help-five-desc: In case of a dispute, we first encourage direct resolution between parties. If unresolved, you can escalate the issue to us, and we'll mediate based on our policies and the evidence provided.
text-help-six-title: Can I cancel a swap after agreeing?
text-help-six-desc: Once a swap has been agreed upon and the deposit has been paid, users are not able to cancel the swap unless there is an issue with the item that warrants a dispute. To initiate a dispute due to problems with the item or to report suspicious activities, please utilize the 'Request Refund' feature available on the user's profile or the item page, or reach out to us directly via our support page for assistance.
text-help-seven-title: How do I contact another swapper?
text-help-seven-desc: After initiating a swap, you can use our secure real-time chat feature to communicate directly with the other party for details and negotiation.
text-help-eight-title: How do I report a problem or suspicious activity?
text-help-eight-desc: If you encounter any problems or suspicious activities, please use the 'Report' feature on the user's profile or item page, or contact us directly through our support page.
text-license-one-desc: "ShwupIt" invites you into the world of seamless item swapping, offering a unique platform for users to exchange goods efficiently and securely. By utilizing our services, you agree to the terms set forth in this Licensing Agreement ('Agreement'), ensuring a trustworthy trading environment for all involved.
text-license-two-desc: Upon agreeing to a swap ('Shwup'), participants are required to deposit an amount equivalent to their item's value. This deposit is safeguarded until the swap concludes successfully. Failure to complete the swap, due to non-delivery or misrepresentation, results in the forfeiture of the deposit to the aggrieved party, along with potential suspension from our platform.
text-license-three-desc: A non-refundable service fee of 5% is deducted from the deposits of both parties at each swap's conclusion. Should a swap not be fulfilled, a 5% penalty is imposed on the forfeited deposit, with the remainder awarded to the compliant party. These measures are crucial for maintaining a secure and reliable trading environment.
text-license-four-desc: Our platform enhances your trading experience through features like the 'Swap It' button for initiating trades, a dynamic Trading Panel for listing items, and a Real-Time Negotiation Chat for seamless communication. Engage in trade with confidence, supported by our comprehensive Trade Matching and Reputation System.
text-license-five-desc: Users are expected to conduct trades truthfully and responsibly. Misrepresentation or failing to honor a swap agreement may lead to deposit forfeiture and account suspension. We encourage all users to adhere to these guidelines to ensure a fair and enjoyable trading experience for everyone.
text-license-six-desc: Shwupit reserves the right to terminate your access to the Service for any violation of this Agreement or engagement in fraudulent activities. Termination may result in the forfeiture of any deposits and the permanent deletion of your account.
text-license-seven-desc: This Agreement may be updated or amended by Shwupit at any time without prior notice. Continued use of the Service after any changes indicates your acceptance of the new terms.
text-license-eight-desc: This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the jurisdiction in which Shwupit is registered, without giving effect to any principles of conflicts of law.
text-license-nine-desc: Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement or the use of the Service shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the arbitration rules of the jurisdiction in which Shwupit is registered.
text-license-ten-desc: If any provision of this Agreement is deemed unlawful, void, or for any reason unenforceable, then that provision shall be deemed severable from this Agreement and shall not affect the validity and enforceability of any remaining provisions.
text-license-eleven-desc: For questions or concerns regarding this Agreement, please contact us at info@shwupit.com. Your feedback is important to us, and we are committed to improving your experience on our platform.
text-privacy-one-desc: This Privacy Policy outlines how ShwupIt ('we', 'us', 'our') collects, uses, and protects the information of the users ('you', 'your') of the ShwupIt website and services ('Platform'). By accessing or using our Platform, you consent to the data practices described in this policy.
text-privacy-two-desc: We collect both Personal Identification Information (PII) and Non-Personal Identification Information (Non-PII) from you. PII includes, but is not limited to, your name, email address, and physical address. Non-PII includes browsing data and usage statistics, which do not identify you personally.
text-privacy-three-desc: Your information allows us to provide, improve, and personalize our services. This includes facilitating swaps, communication between users, and improving user experience. We also use your information for security purposes, to comply with legal obligations, and to inform you of changes to our services.
text-privacy-four-desc: We do not sell, trade, or rent your PII to others. We may share generic aggregated demographic information not linked to any PII with our business partners, trusted affiliates, and advertisers. We may also disclose your information when legally required to do so, to protect our rights, or to enforce our site policies.
text-privacy-five-desc: Our Platform utilizes 'cookies' and other tracking technologies to enhance user experience and analyze trends. You can choose to disable cookies through your browser, but this may limit your use of certain features on our Platform.
text-privacy-six-desc: We adopt appropriate data collection, storage, and processing practices and security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your personal information and data stored on our Platform.
text-privacy-seven-desc: You have rights regarding the personal information we hold about you, including the right to access, correct, or request deletion of your personal data. For any such requests, please contact us directly.
text-privacy-eight-desc: ShwupIt does not knowingly collect or solicit information from anyone under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will delete that information as quickly as possible.
text-privacy-nine-desc: We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
text-privacy-ten-desc: If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, the practices of this site, or your dealings with this site, please contact us at: info@shwupit.com
text-terms-one-desc: Welcome to ShwupIt! We offer a unique platform for users to swap items effortlessly. By using ShwupIt, you agree to our Terms and Conditions outlined herein. ShwupIt is operated by ShwupIt Private Limited, a company duly incorporated under the Companies Act, with its headquarters in Ireland
text-terms-two-desc: To participate in ShwupIt's swapping ecosystem, users must be 18 years or older or have legal parental or guardian consent. By using our services, you affirm that you meet these eligibility requirements.
text-terms-three-desc: Users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their account and password and for all activities that occur under their account. You agree to notify ShwupIt immediately of any unauthorized use of your account.
text-terms-four-desc: ShwupIt prohibits the listing and swapping of illegal items, stolen goods, and items that infringe on intellectual property rights. Users engaging in such activities will face account suspension or termination.
text-terms-five-desc: Upon agreeing to a swap, both parties are required to deposit an amount equivalent to the value of the items involved. A non-refundable service fee of 5% is applied to each successful swap.
text-terms-six-desc: In the event of a dispute, ShwupIt encourages users to first seek a resolution amongst themselves. If unresolved, ShwupIt reserves the right to mediate and make a final decision based on available evidence.
text-terms-seven-desc: All content included on ShwupIt, such as text, graphics, logos, images, and software, is the property of ShwupIt or its content suppliers and protected by international copyright laws.
text-terms-eight-desc: ShwupIt reserves the right to amend these Terms and Conditions at any time. Users will be notified of any changes through our platform updates or via email.
text-terms-nine-desc: These Terms and Conditions shall be governed by the laws of the jurisdiction where ShwupIt Private Limited is registered. Any disputes will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of that jurisdiction.
text-terms-ten-desc: For any inquiries or concerns regarding these Terms and Conditions, please reach out to us via the Contact Us page on our website.
